Black Nugget Farms
With honey bees dying at the rate of 50% and demand for honey and bees products increasing
dramatically, how are retailers meeting these current demands and providing all natural Bee
products? Many arent! A large number of Bee products sold by larger retailers are cut with
sugar and corn syrup or sources from China that use antibiotics banned by many countries.
Wholesalers buy bulk honey from sources where they cannot confirm the quality.
Buy your Bee products locally and know the sources.
Black Nugget Farms is a small, local bee farm. Black Nugget Farms owns 300 bee hives and is
one of the largest Bee Keepers on the Eastside. Our bees travel throughout the spring and
summer. They go up to Bellingham for apples and blueberries and to the mountains around the
Puget Sound for fireweed. They winter at small bee yards around The Sound where they rest
and hibernate.
The products we sell are 100% from our bees. I hope you enjoy our all natural honey and wax
products.
